<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="177" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="177">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="177">
Both records presented here are new locality data with original coordinates. However, they clearly correspond with the known species range in Afghanistan. 
<bibRefCitation pageId="0" pageNumber="177" refId="B14">Regan (2017)</bibRefCitation>
listed this species as &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesalina guttulata" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guttulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">Mesalina guttulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (pp. 30-31). This name was superseded by 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. watsonana" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" rank="species" species="watsonana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">M. watsonana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after being upgraded to full species status from a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. guttulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" rank="species" species="guttulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">M. guttulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
